  "text": "In this paper we make a step in applying the general framework described above. Our main result provides randomized k-server algorithms for a natural class of metric spaces defined on unweighted graphs having bounded growth-rate, including d-dimensional grids. The growth-rate (see [CITATION_1] ) of an unweighted graph M is ρ = max{log |B(x, r)|/ log r; x ∈ M, r ≥ 2}. Such metric spaces can be probabilistically approximated by HSTs with some special properties that enable us to get better algorithms. The competitive ratio we obtain for the class of growth-rate ρ is ∆",
